21:46.521 --> 21:48.187
Do you know where he is?

21:51.359 --> 21:55.207
- Who are you?
- Good question.

21:56.331 --> 21:57.947
We work together.

22:01.786 --> 22:03.502
He'll be home soon.

22:03.538 --> 22:05.755
Just called me from
the car ten minutes ago.

22:05.790 --> 22:08.040
He's stuck in some traffic.

22:08.042 --> 22:10.259
You're welcome to wait
inside if you want.

22:10.295 --> 22:12.211
Whoo! Oh, shit!

22:12.213 --> 22:14.130
- Come on, get up!
- Fsociety, bitch!

22:14.182 --> 22:17.044
- Yeah, that's how it is, baby!
- Whoo!

22:21.570 --> 22:23.222
What did you say your name was?

22:25.643 --> 22:28.728
Uh... I'm Ollie.

22:30.948 --> 22:33.566
And what were you working
on with my husband?

22:33.618 --> 22:35.735
You've gotta help
me get out of this.

22:35.737 --> 22:37.236
There's something about her.

22:37.238 --> 22:38.788
I feel like she can hear us.

22:38.823 --> 22:41.040
He wanted my advice,

22:41.075 --> 22:45.578
you know, about the hack
that's going on right now.

22:45.580 --> 22:47.496
When was the last time you saw him?

22:50.001 --> 22:52.718
She's lying to me. He isn't coming.

22:52.754 --> 22:55.588
She's fishing for something.

22:55.590 --> 22:58.474
I'm not sure.

22:58.509 --> 23:01.260
It was last week, I think.

23:01.262 --> 23:03.479
Really?

23:06.351 --> 23:10.770
You know, between you and me,

23:10.772 --> 23:14.440
I'm a little concerned for Tyrell.

23:14.492 --> 23:16.992
Was he acting strange when you saw him?

23:19.831 --> 23:23.616
No.

23:23.618 --> 23:26.001
That's funny,

23:26.037 --> 23:29.038
'cause he was acting very strange

23:29.090 --> 23:31.841
last I saw him.

23:31.876 --> 23:33.676
Three days ago.

23:35.849 --> 23:38.165
Didn't she say he just called?

23:38.800 --> 23:40.132
And then he just vanished.

23:48.476 --> 23:52.027
Excuse me?

23:52.063 --> 23:53.813
I don't understand what you're saying.

24:02.240 --> 24:09.144
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. I think it's just the stress

24:09.145 --> 24:12.965
from the past few days getting to me.

24:13.000 --> 24:15.584
Anyway, I shouldn't take
up any more of your time.

24:18.055 --> 24:22.057
Thank you... Ollie.

24:49.203 --> 24:50.920
And, Sarah, we've had meetings all weekend

24:50.955 --> 24:53.038
handling the situation.

24:53.090 --> 24:54.757
I'm being told by our network storage team

24:54.792 --> 24:57.259
that they are in fact
getting to the bottom of this.

24:57.295 --> 24:59.879
Mr. Plouffe, have you seen
the latest stock price?

24:59.931 --> 25:02.181
It's hitting an all-time low of $18,

25:02.216 --> 25:03.883
and it's still dropping.

25:03.885 --> 25:06.385
How are people reacting
to this on the inside?

25:06.437 --> 25:10.556
Almost $400 billion of
wealth was lost today.

25:10.608 --> 25:14.610
That's pretty astounding.
Are you concerned?

25:14.645 --> 25:16.729
That's an interesting question.

25:16.731 --> 25:18.731
But right now we're focused on tackling

25:18.733 --> 25:20.616
the technical issues at hand.

25:20.651 --> 25:22.568
We have loyal customers who are suffering,

25:22.620 --> 25:25.538
and our number one priority
is to address their needs.

25:25.573 --> 25:27.907
We had one of our experts
in here earlier today.

25:27.959 --> 25:29.575
They're saying that if, in fact,

25:29.577 --> 25:31.494
fsociety's claims are true...

25:31.546 --> 25:33.078
Your data is inaccessible

25:33.080 --> 25:35.748
and could prove nearly
impossible to recover.

25:35.750 --> 25:38.083
And given that there does seem
to be some legitimacy to this...

25:38.135 --> 25:41.086
The White House is with us on this.

25:41.088 --> 25:42.755
They're gonna protect everyone's money.

25:42.757 --> 25:45.474
The bottom line is

25:45.510 --> 25:48.427
the public does not
need to worry about this.

25:48.429 --> 25:50.896
Mr. Plouffe, this
was a massive attack.

25:50.932 --> 25:54.233
All of your servers, including
your data center in China

25:54.268 --> 25:56.902
as well as your offline
backups have been destroyed.

25:56.938 --> 26:00.439
I'm not really sure you can
ask the public not to worry.

26:12.370 --> 26:14.286
- You want me to be honest?
- Of course.

26:14.338 --> 26:18.090
You're right. Absolutely right.

26:18.125 --> 26:21.293
The public should be worried.

26:21.345 --> 26:25.431
I mean, personally, my life is over.

26:25.466 --> 26:27.099
What's happening?

26:27.134 --> 26:31.303
My pension, savings, everything...

26:31.305 --> 26:33.606
has been in this company
since I started here,

26:33.641 --> 26:37.476
and that's all gone now.

26:37.478 --> 26:40.145
Truth is...

26:40.197 --> 26:42.982
I've been with the
engineering team all weekend.

26:43.034 --> 26:45.117
This has to stop. That's enough.

26:45.152 --> 26:46.819
No one knows how to fix it.

26:48.656 --> 26:52.157
In fact, about the only
thing we do know for certain

26:52.159 --> 26:55.628
is that...

26:55.663 --> 26:59.665
this will be impossible to fix.

26:59.717 --> 27:01.884
You need to take care of this.

27:12.013 --> 27:15.848
Calm down, everyone.

27:25.396 --> 27:27.397
That's all we need from
Ms. Moss, Mr. Price.

27:27.399 --> 27:29.132
- Good. Thank you.
- Sir.

27:29.134 --> 27:30.600
Thanks.

27:41.479 --> 27:45.681
I heard you were leaving for the day.

27:45.683 --> 27:50.419
Mr. Price...

27:50.421 --> 27:55.658
- did you need me to stay?
- No, no, no, no. Sit, sit.

27:55.659 --> 27:57.910
I know I'm the CEO of the company,

27:57.912 --> 28:00.963
but what you went
through, it was traumatic.

28:00.965 --> 28:05.217
I just felt I needed to
make myself available.

28:05.219 --> 28:07.837
You are absolutely free to... to go home

28:07.839 --> 28:13.059
and... and recover, of course.

28:13.061 --> 28:16.095
All right?

28:18.850 --> 28:21.100
Oh.

28:21.102 --> 28:25.354
You're Terry's reference, right?

28:27.158 --> 28:30.326
I rarely see him impressed
with anyone, but you... you?

28:30.328 --> 28:34.947
Well... we're glad you're on the team.

28:34.949 --> 28:39.785
And I look forward to
you impressing me as well.

28:39.787 --> 28:42.371
You know, I'm... I'm
holding a press conference

28:42.373 --> 28:44.040
this afternoon.

28:44.042 --> 28:45.624
Since you're new to the PR department,

28:45.626 --> 28:47.176
I think you should attend.

28:47.178 --> 28:50.212
You might pick up some invaluable lessons.

28:52.517 --> 28:56.802
Um...

28:56.804 --> 28:59.221
no.

28:59.223 --> 29:02.692
No, I'm not sure that I can.

29:06.114 --> 29:10.700
Well, the invitation is open

29:10.702 --> 29:13.736
if you should change your mind.

29:16.240 --> 29:18.574
Um...

29:27.251 --> 29:29.418
You need some new shoes.

29:29.420 --> 29:31.804
Those won't do anymore.

30:10.545 --> 30:12.211
Tyrell Wellick's gone.

30:12.213 --> 30:15.840
I wake up in his SUV and the
world's about to fall apart.

30:25.526 --> 30:27.143
I know. I know this looks bad,

30:27.145 --> 30:29.258
but I'm sure there's an explanation.

30:30.398 --> 30:32.231
Don't think that. We'll find him.

30:32.233 --> 30:34.617
We'll find him. He's
gotta be somewhere.

30:34.619 --> 30:37.119
My dad, Mr. Robot,
whatever the hell he is,

30:37.121 --> 30:39.789
if he's not gonna show
up, maybe he got sloppy,

30:39.791 --> 30:42.662
left behind a clue.

30:42.663 --> 30:44.905
_

31:17.161 --> 31:21.197
All right, come out!

31:21.199 --> 31:22.865
Come out now!

31:26.204 --> 31:29.622
Come on!

31:29.624 --> 31:32.541
I need to know what happened!

31:32.543 --> 31:34.627
Come on out!

31:34.629 --> 31:36.629
I'm here!

31:36.631 --> 31:39.515
I'm waiting for you!

31:39.517 --> 31:41.684
Come on, man.

31:41.686 --> 31:43.219
Come out!

31:43.221 --> 31:46.722
Okay, we have to go analog for this.

31:46.724 --> 31:48.891
We need to get these fliers out now

31:48.893 --> 31:52.061
since we can't be sure anyone's
Internet access will work.

31:56.817 --> 32:00.319
What? I'm thinking ahead.

32:00.321 --> 32:03.072
First banking, then infrastructure.

32:03.074 --> 32:05.824
We've been through this.

32:05.826 --> 32:09.044
Now, take these fliers, pass them out.

32:09.046 --> 32:13.215
It's the last step and then we're clear.

32:13.217 --> 32:16.752
You guys are acting like we're
walking towards doomsday here.

32:16.754 --> 32:19.471
Well, it does say here

32:19.473 --> 32:24.176
it's an end of the world party.

32:24.178 --> 32:26.178
Figure of speech.

32:32.069 --> 32:34.186
You wonder why we're
not in high spirits?

32:34.188 --> 32:35.938
Maybe it's because our fearless leader goes

32:35.940 --> 32:38.274
and shoots up the world
and then disappears,

32:38.276 --> 32:41.493
yet again, while we're
here cleaning up after him.

32:53.372 --> 32:55.860
_

33:19.150 --> 33:21.567
He knows the password,

33:21.569 --> 33:24.283
which means I know the password.

33:30.653 --> 33:33.137
_

34:05.112 --> 34:07.529
What's he trying to say?

34:07.531 --> 34:10.616
I'm on the hook for everything?

34:18.009 --> 34:20.842
He won't come out to play if I ask.

34:20.844 --> 34:23.879
So maybe I gotta force his hand.

34:25.599 --> 34:27.549
I need to use a landline.

34:27.551 --> 34:30.552
I need to get myself arrested.

34:35.693 --> 34:39.554
- 911. What's your emergency?
- I have a confession to make.

34:40.731 --> 34:43.565
All right, you got me.

34:43.567 --> 34:46.235
I'm afraid to ask.

34:46.237 --> 34:49.288
Now, wait a minute, you said you work...

34:51.909 --> 34:56.078
Was this from the guy?

34:56.080 --> 35:00.165
The one they're talking about on the news?

35:00.167 --> 35:05.137
Um... yes.

35:09.226 --> 35:15.147
You mean to tell me you
witnessed this thing...

35:15.149 --> 35:17.733
and you're here to buy new shoes?

35:22.857 --> 35:25.991
Wow.

35:25.993 --> 35:28.944
That's pretty...

35:28.946 --> 35:31.663
It's just pretty cold.

35:31.665 --> 35:34.249
How can you work there?

35:34.251 --> 35:36.335
That guy said it himself,
they're just liars.

35:36.337 --> 35:40.255
I know. They are.

35:40.257 --> 35:43.342
But I'm not sure

35:43.344 --> 35:45.461
that he knew what he was saying.

35:45.463 --> 35:47.296
Oh, you sound just like them.

35:47.298 --> 35:51.350
Have some moral fiber
and leave their asses.

35:51.352 --> 35:53.469
Their practices are well-documented

35:53.471 --> 35:55.637
and it's all despicable.

35:55.639 --> 35:58.056
Listen, this isn't my business,

35:58.058 --> 35:59.775
but don't drink their Kool-Aid.

35:59.777 --> 36:01.977
Look, I just needed a job.

36:01.979 --> 36:03.312
What kind of an excuse is that?

36:03.314 --> 36:05.364
- You don't understand.
- You should hear yourself.

36:05.366 --> 36:07.581
I don't know who you
think you're talking to,

36:07.582 --> 36:10.235
but I'll try the Pradas next.

36:34.228 --> 36:36.979
Calm down.

36:36.981 --> 36:40.349
Get your caramel latte. It's on me.

36:40.351 --> 36:43.685
- Where is he?
- You know how this looks, right?

36:43.686 --> 36:45.437
Very weird.

36:49.693 --> 36:51.432
I don't give a shit.

36:51.433 --> 36:55.998
- Where's Tyrell?
- We made a deal that helped us both.

36:56.000 --> 36:58.700
Tell me where he is!

36:58.702 --> 37:00.252
You're starting to attract some attention.

37:00.254 --> 37:02.621
I recommend you get one of
those Bluetooth headsets.

37:02.623 --> 37:04.506
That way people just think
you're the local douche.

37:04.508 --> 37:06.758
Tyrell disappeared.

37:06.760 --> 37:10.546
No one knows where he is.

37:10.548 --> 37:11.713
But you know.

37:14.969 --> 37:17.936
So do you.

37:17.938 --> 37:20.522
You forget, kiddo, I am you.

37:23.027 --> 37:27.082
- No, you're not.
- Is that a fact?

37:40.411 --> 37:43.879
Hey, man, I gotta tell you I had
sex with your mom this morning,

37:43.881 --> 37:45.297
and it was fantastic.

37:48.002 --> 37:51.086
Don't have time for you, little man.

37:51.088 --> 37:54.256
Your mom was real nice. Smell.

37:54.258 --> 37:56.425
God! What did you do to him?

37:56.427 --> 37:58.143
What did I do?

37:58.145 --> 37:59.478
Well, did you just see what he did?

37:59.480 --> 38:01.396
- No, I don't know, man.
- Yeah, he flicked my nose.

38:05.753 --> 38:08.170
You're losing it, kiddo.

38:11.542 --> 38:13.875
I'm only supposed to be your prophet.

38:13.877 --> 38:17.021
You're supposed to be my god.

38:17.721 --> 38:19.069
Come on!

38:19.291 --> 38:22.210
The dramatic repercussions of
the recent financial meltdown

38:22.245 --> 38:24.412
are not relegated to
developing nations.

38:24.464 --> 38:27.081
The United States has also
witnessed a disruption

38:27.133 --> 38:28.833
of order and peace.

38:28.835 --> 38:31.636
While businesses determine how
or whether they will function

38:31.671 --> 38:34.088
through the uncertainty,
individuals have taken

38:34.140 --> 38:36.891
to the streets, giving the
major cities a tenor...

38:36.927 --> 38:39.260
Ooh.

38:39.312 --> 38:41.679
Very nice.

38:41.681 --> 38:43.431
I'm glad you reconsidered.

38:47.931 --> 38:50.271
What? What is it?

38:50.323 --> 38:53.024
Come on.

38:53.026 --> 38:54.859
You have questions.

38:54.911 --> 38:56.995
I'm a person with a lot of answers,

38:57.030 --> 38:59.197
especially right now.

39:02.085 --> 39:05.703
Okay.

39:05.755 --> 39:09.874
It's just that...

39:09.926 --> 39:13.594
well, I can't help but wonder,

39:13.630 --> 39:15.847
why do you seem so confident?

39:18.551 --> 39:22.437
Everyone else is worried, but you?

39:22.472 --> 39:25.606
You're sure that you're
gonna get through this.

39:25.642 --> 39:28.643
- Why?
- Hmm.

39:33.450 --> 39:37.500
- People did this. Right?
- _

39:37.501 --> 39:40.621
I mean, aliens didn't
invade our planet.

39:40.657 --> 39:43.041
Zeus didn't come out of
the heavens to destroy us.

39:43.076 --> 39:46.133
Zombies haven't risen from the dead.

39:46.647 --> 39:48.913
No.

39:48.965 --> 39:51.165
Whoever's behind this,

39:51.217 --> 39:53.751
they're just people...

39:53.753 --> 39:58.172
like you and me.

39:58.224 --> 40:00.091
Except, of course, I have the full weight

40:00.093 --> 40:03.594
of the biggest conglomerate
in the world behind me.

40:03.646 --> 40:06.981
You'll come to realize
that when you have that,

40:07.017 --> 40:12.020
matters like this, they tend to crack...

40:12.072 --> 40:14.381
under that weight.

40:16.943 --> 40:20.452
Can I ask another question?

40:20.453 --> 40:24.115
All right, go.

40:24.167 --> 40:26.451
Why me?

40:26.453 --> 40:30.538
Why am I really here?

40:30.590 --> 40:32.590
I know you know who I am.

40:32.625 --> 40:35.543
Why are you letting me be here?

40:35.595 --> 40:39.881
Why are you even talking to me right now?

40:39.933 --> 40:42.266
None of this makes any sense.

40:42.302 --> 40:46.437
Well, be that as it may, I...

40:46.473 --> 40:49.440
I find you refreshing.

40:49.476 --> 40:52.810
You're young, bold,

40:52.862 --> 40:57.031
exactly what we need right now.

40:57.067 --> 40:59.400
- Come on.
- What?

40:59.452 --> 41:02.236
There has to be more to it than that.

41:02.288 --> 41:05.706
Angela, just a word of advice.

41:05.742 --> 41:08.326
Don't talk your way out of a compliment.

41:08.328 --> 41:11.796
Excuse me. They'll be ready.

41:11.831 --> 41:13.831
Shall we?

41:21.341 --> 41:25.143
Oh, you're still thinking
about this morning.

41:27.680 --> 41:30.681
I don't think I'll ever get
that image out of my head.

41:33.520 --> 41:37.155
Between you and me, I was
glad he killed himself.

41:39.109 --> 41:40.608
He was not a very good person.

41:40.660 --> 41:42.693
He had a gambling problem.

41:42.745 --> 41:44.328
He drank too much.

41:44.364 --> 41:47.115
Most notably, he was weak.

41:47.167 --> 41:49.667
His instincts left a lot to be desired.

41:49.702 --> 41:53.421
Oh, I despise people like that.

41:53.456 --> 41:57.091
In fact, I felt...

41:57.127 --> 42:01.179
the world was a little better off

42:01.214 --> 42:05.633
knowing he wasn't in it anymore.

42:05.685 --> 42:09.887
Oh, I believe even his
family will benefit from this

42:09.939 --> 42:12.223
in the long run.

42:28.208 --> 42:30.791
Before we even begin,

42:30.827 --> 42:33.411
let's have a moment of silence

42:33.463 --> 42:37.131
for our dear, brave friend,

42:37.167 --> 42:39.634
James Plouffe.

42:54.734 --> 42:57.068
Well, this place is a petri dish now.

42:57.103 --> 43:00.321
Yeah, I'd say we got enough
fingerprints everywhere.

43:00.356 --> 43:02.406
So that's it then, right?

43:02.442 --> 43:04.575
That's it?

43:04.611 --> 43:07.612
That's it?

43:07.614 --> 43:10.615
How about, "That's amazing"?

43:10.667 --> 43:12.617
How about we party

43:12.669 --> 43:15.286
and thank ourselves for
all the hard work we did?

43:15.338 --> 43:18.766
Yeah, I don't think Trenton
was talking about tonight.

43:19.152 --> 43:21.443
- Well, what then?
- Well, you know,

43:21.444 --> 43:23.346
I think she's saying after tonight, right?

43:23.347 --> 43:26.655
Then what? I mean, what do we all do now?

43:26.656 --> 43:30.268
Guys, this isn't about
what we'll do tomorrow!

43:30.303 --> 43:31.969
This is about what we did.

43:32.021 --> 43:34.472
I mean, look at all these people.

43:34.524 --> 43:38.142
They're free because of us,

43:38.144 --> 43:41.812
because of what we did in this room.

43:41.864 --> 43:44.732
We're finally awake!

43:51.291 --> 43:53.908
We are finally alive.

43:56.231 --> 43:58.168
- Our streets!
- Whose streets?

43:58.169 --> 44:00.061
- Our streets!
- Whose streets?

44:00.062 --> 44:01.462
- Our streets!
- Whose streets?

44:01.464 --> 44:02.579
Our streets!

44:02.581 --> 44:04.248
- Whose streets?
- Our streets!

44:04.250 --> 44:06.133
- Whose streets?
- Our streets!

44:06.135 --> 44:08.085
- Whose streets?
- Our streets!

44:08.087 --> 44:10.905
- I know you killed him.
- Our streets!

44:10.906 --> 44:13.193
I know you did it. I know you did it.

44:13.195 --> 44:15.279
Just tell me what happened to Tyrell.

44:15.281 --> 44:18.125
- Our streets!
- Shut up!

44:18.367 --> 44:20.534
I have played nice for far too long.

44:20.536 --> 44:22.202
I'm so sick of your whining.

44:22.204 --> 44:24.538
It's not gonna change anything anyway.

44:24.540 --> 44:27.841
Please, you have to do something.

44:27.843 --> 44:29.376
You have to help me.

44:29.378 --> 44:32.464
- Say something. Make him tell me.
- Stop talking to them!

44:32.882 --> 44:34.882
They can't help us.

44:34.884 --> 44:37.134
We have to do this together, just us.

44:37.136 --> 44:39.887
He's right, you know.

44:41.691 --> 44:45.643
You're hurting the
whole family, Elliot.

44:45.645 --> 44:48.562
No, no, this isn't my family.

44:48.564 --> 44:50.481
None of them are real.

44:50.483 --> 44:52.533
Neither is whoever you're talking to.

44:55.237 --> 44:57.821
Then you're not real.

44:57.823 --> 45:00.457
You're not real.

45:00.459 --> 45:02.743
What? You are?

45:02.745 --> 45:05.713
Is any of it real?

45:05.715 --> 45:09.500
I mean, look at this. Look at it!

45:09.502 --> 45:12.086
A world built on fantasy!

45:12.088 --> 45:13.921
Synthetic emotions in the form of pills,

45:13.923 --> 45:17.341
psychological warfare in
the form of advertising,

45:17.343 --> 45:20.728
mind-altering chemicals
in the form of food,

45:20.730 --> 45:23.063
brainwashing seminars in the form of media,

45:23.065 --> 45:26.433
controlled isolated bubbles
in the form of social networks.

45:26.435 --> 45:29.353
Real? You want to talk about reality?

45:29.355 --> 45:32.189
We haven't lived in
anything remotely close to it

45:32.191 --> 45:33.607
since the turn of the century.

45:33.609 --> 45:35.442
We turned it off, took out the batteries,

45:35.444 --> 45:37.578
snacked on a bag of GMOs

45:37.580 --> 45:40.781
while we tossed the remnants
in the ever-expanding dumpster

45:40.783 --> 45:42.616
of the human condition.

45:42.618 --> 45:45.285
We live in branded houses
trademarked by corporations

45:45.287 --> 45:47.588
built on bipolar numbers

45:47.590 --> 45:50.541
jumping up and down on digital displays,

45:50.543 --> 45:54.128
hypnotizing us into the biggest
slumber mankind has ever seen.

45:54.130 --> 45:55.963
You have to dig pretty deep, kiddo,

45:55.965 --> 45:57.965
before you can find anything real.

45:57.967 --> 46:00.384
We live in a kingdom of bullshit,

46:00.386 --> 46:02.636
a kingdom you've lived in for far too long.

46:02.638 --> 46:05.973
So don't tell me about not being real.

46:05.975 --> 46:07.608
I'm no less real than
the fucking beef patty

46:07.610 --> 46:09.226
in your...

46:09.228 --> 46:10.894
As far as you're concerned, Elliot,

46:10.896 --> 46:12.613
I am very real.

46:12.615 --> 46:15.649
We are all together now,
whether you like it or not.

46:21.791 --> 46:25.659
No! No!

46:25.661 --> 46:27.661
No!

46:33.169 --> 46:36.720
I want to be alone.

46:36.722 --> 46:38.088
I need to be alone.

47:23.469 --> 47:26.239
No, you don't want that, remember?

47:28.390 --> 47:30.891
Remember how you felt
when you were alone?

47:30.893 --> 47:32.726
You were in pain.
You were miserable.

47:32.728 --> 47:37.147
That's why we're here.

47:37.149 --> 47:39.199
Those lonely nights
when you sat and cried

47:39.201 --> 47:43.153
in your apartment, you
begged us to help you.

47:43.155 --> 47:45.906
You asked us to come.
You needed us to come.

47:45.908 --> 47:48.292
No!

47:48.294 --> 47:51.044
I want you to leave!

47:51.046 --> 47:52.329
Leave!

47:52.331 --> 47:54.047
We're deep down inside you, Elliot.

47:54.049 --> 47:57.835
You can't leave us,
and we can't leave you.

47:57.837 --> 47:59.386
Ever.

47:59.388 --> 48:01.839
It's true, Son.

48:06.428 --> 48:10.097
I don't know what I'm supposed to do.

48:16.272 --> 48:18.739
I'll tell you exactly
what you're gonna do.

48:18.741 --> 48:21.275
You're gonna start listening to us.

48:21.277 --> 48:24.444
The world is a better place
because of what we did, Elliot,

48:24.446 --> 48:27.581
and you're gonna realize
that one way or another.

48:27.583 --> 48:29.867
Now, here's what I
need you to do now.

48:32.288 --> 48:34.755
You're going to walk to the subway.

48:39.929 --> 48:42.296
You're going to get on your train.

48:59.031 --> 49:01.949
You're going to get
off at your stop.

49:01.951 --> 49:04.117
Woohoo-hoo-hoo!

49:08.958 --> 49:10.490
You're going to go home.

49:16.332 --> 49:18.665
You're gonna sit at your computer,

49:18.667 --> 49:20.834
watch and enjoy the
beautiful carnage

49:20.836 --> 49:23.804
that we've all created together.

49:23.806 --> 49:27.174
We hope a new society
rises from the ashes,

49:27.176 --> 49:29.343
that you will forge a better world.

51:47.149 --> 51:49.566
- Well, enjoy the evening.
- Thank you.

51:53.906 --> 51:55.789
- How are you?
- Good evening.

51:55.791 --> 51:57.707
- Good to see you.
- Thank you.

52:23.185 --> 52:27.070
Go ahead. What's on your mind?

52:27.072 --> 52:30.190
I know you're not without your troubles,

52:30.192 --> 52:33.860
but we still haven't
discussed the coltan mines.

52:33.862 --> 52:36.196
You're really bringing
that up at a time like this?

52:36.198 --> 52:39.950
You asked, I answered, succinctly.

52:39.952 --> 52:43.203
Well, perhaps I was too hasty.

52:43.205 --> 52:46.873
I'd like, for the moment,
to take in the music.

52:46.875 --> 52:50.844
Besides... plenty of
other items on our agenda.

52:50.846 --> 52:53.213
The fucking Congo can wait.

52:53.215 --> 52:57.801
Oh, your troubles are
weighing heavily on you.

52:57.803 --> 52:59.803
I'm not entirely sure why.

52:59.805 --> 53:03.023
I was told that you know
the person responsible.

53:03.025 --> 53:06.026
Yes. Yes.

53:06.028 --> 53:09.896
Of course we do.

53:09.898 --> 53:13.150
And we will handle that person

53:13.152 --> 53:15.068
as we usually do.

53:22.327 --> 53:28.081
- You seem a little preoccupied yourself.
- I don't believe in preoccupation.

53:30.085 --> 53:32.085
It's more of an observation.

53:32.087 --> 53:35.347
- Which is?
- The infamous Emperor Nero

53:35.348 --> 53:39.505
played an instrument very similar
to the one she's playing, the lyre.

53:40.596 --> 53:42.692
Legend has it that he played it merrily

53:42.693 --> 53:46.600
as he watched...

53:46.602 --> 53:52.251
- As he watched?
- As he watched Rome burn.

